S%20exposure%20in%20humans%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Megan%20Romano%2C%20corresponding%20author%20and%20Associate%20Professor%20of%20Epidemiology%20at%20Dartmouth%20College's%20Geisel%20School%20of%20Medicine%20in%20the%20UK.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUnderstanding%20this%20risk-benefit%20trade-off%20for%20seafood%20consumption%20is%20important%20for%20people%20making%20decisions%20about%20diet%2C%20especially%20for%20vulnerable%20populations%20such%20as%20pregnant%20women%20and%20children%2C%26quot%3B%20Romano%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20study%2C%20the%20team%20measured%20the%20levels%20of%2026%20varieties%20of%20PFAS%20in%20samples%20of%20the%20most%20consumed%20marine%20species%3A%20cod%2C%20haddock%2C%20lobster%2C%20salmon%2C%20scallop%2C%20shrimp%20and%20tuna.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20findings%2C%20published%20in%20the%20journal%20Exposure%20and%20Health%2C%20showed%20that%20shrimp%20and%20lobster%20carry%20the%20highest%20concentrations%20with%20averages%20ranging%20as%20high%20as%201.74%20and%203.30%20nanograms%20per%20gram%20of%20flesh%2C%20respectively%2C%20for%20certain%20PFAS%20compounds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPFAS%2C%20which%20break%20down%20very%20slowly%20over%20time%20and%20can%20persist%20over%20thousands%20of%20years%20in%20the%20environment%2C%20are%20potentially%20harmful%20to%20people%2C%20wildlife%2C%20and%20the%20environment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStudies%20have%20shown%20their%20exposure%20raises%20the%20risk%20of%20cancer%2C%20foetal%20abnormalities%2C%20high%20cholesterol%2C%20and%20thyroid%2C%20liver%2C%20and%20reproductive%20disorders%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1713066060000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-04%2Fo5m4vbn8_seafood-generic_625x300_12_April_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience